rc="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2200/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2200&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:21;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:65:"WordPress.tv: WordPress Panel Discussion – WordCamp Dallas 2009";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2189";s:4:"link";s:56:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/06/28/panel-wordpress-dallas09/";s:11:"description";s:1373:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-15">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/06/28/panel-wordpress-dallas09/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/i5hx6Kvc/wcd09-the-panel_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2189&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 29 Jul 2009 01:45:10 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:11:"Ryan Markel";}s:7:"summary";s:1373:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-15">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/06/28/panel-wordpress-dallas09/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/i5hx6Kvc/wcd09-the-panel_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2189/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2189&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:22;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:56:"Weblog Tools Collection: Do you use the WordPress Codex?";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6316";s:4:"link";s:84:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/28/do-you-use-the-wordpress-codex/";s:11:"description";s:1469:"<p>Jeff and I have been having some interesting discussions surrounding the <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Main_Page">WordPress Codex</a> and WordPress documentation. In case you were not aware, there is some fantastic volunteering work going on in WordPress documentation. We would like to see more people involved in the use of and help with the Codex and have some ideas up our sleeves towards that end. However, I think we also need to know what we are dealing with and would like some input from our readers.</p>\n<p>I see two different audiences of the Codex and thus the two separate polls. Comments are also appreciated. Let us know if you want to help with the Codex or if you would like to help with WordPress documentation.</p>\n<p><center><br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://answers.polldaddy.com/poll/1818711/">You are a Blogger. How often do you use the WordPress Codex?</a><span>(<a href="http://www.polldaddy.com">online surveys</a>)</span><br />\n</p>\n<p><br />\n<a href="http://answers.polldaddy.com/poll/1818686/">You are a Developer/Designer. How often do you use the WordPress Codex?</a><span>(<a href="http://www.polldaddy.com">online surveys</a>)</span><br />\n<br />\n</center></p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/28/do-you-use-the-wordpress-codex/">Do you use the WordPress Codex?</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 28 Jul 2009 22:19:16 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:10:"Mark Ghosh";}s:7:"summary";s:1469:"<p>Jeff and I have been having some interesting discussions surrounding the <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Main_Page">WordPress Codex</a> and WordPress documentation. In case you were not aware, there is some fantastic volunteering work going on in WordPress documentation. We would like to see more people involved in the use of and help with the Codex and have some ideas up our sleeves towards that end. However, I think we also need to know what we are dealing with and would like some input from our readers.</p>\n<p>I see two different audiences of the Codex and thus the two separate polls. Comments are also appreciated. Let us know if you want to help with the Codex or if you would like to help with WordPress documentation.</p>\n<p><center><br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://answers.polldaddy.com/poll/1818711/">You are a Blogger. How often do you use the WordPress Codex?</a><span>(<a href="http://www.polldaddy.com">online surveys</a>)</span><br />\n</p>\n<p><br />\n<a href="http://answers.polldaddy.com/poll/1818686/">You are a Developer/Designer. How often do you use the WordPress Codex?</a><span>(<a href="http://www.polldaddy.com">online surveys</a>)</span><br />\n<br />\n</center></p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/28/do-you-use-the-wordpress-codex/">Do you use the WordPress Codex?</a></p>";}i:23;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:43:"WP Blackberry: Beta 0.9.0.140 Available Now";s:4:"guid";s:38:"http://blackberry.wordpress.org/?p=137";s:4:"link";s:66:"http://blackberry.wordpress.org/2009/07/28/beta-140-available-now/";s:11:"description";s:3131:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>Hi everyone !  Things are progressing nicely with this beta test thanks to everyone who has posted on the <a href="http://blackberry.forums.wordpress.org/">forums</a> and on <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/">trac</a>.  We really appreciate all the feedback and time spent by all of you beta testers.</p>\n<p>Today we have a new beta, version 0.9.0.140 for you to <a href="http://blackberry.wordpress.org/install">download</a>.  Changes include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Improving response time of the user interface <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/58">(ticket #58 UI response time</a>)</li>\n<li>Removingthe photo multimedia option in the app because photo settings are managed in the main BlackBerry camera app</li>\n<li>Fixing a bug with <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/57">local drafts (ticket #57)</a></li>\n<li>Adding prompts to save post when clicking <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/59">&#8220;Back&#8221; button (ticket #59)</a></li>\n<li>Fixing a bug involving <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/60">categories (ticket #60)</a></li>\n<li>Fixing how <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/61">private posts were not publishing correctly (ticket #61)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>We are also aware that some of you prefer to use this app connecting with BIS.  We are actively working on a solution for this with RIM, but currently don&#8217;t have an ETA for that.</p>\n<p>And as always, please do no post comments to this post involving support or troubleshooting.  If you are having issues, please first review the <a href="http://blackberry.wordpress.org/faq/">FAQ</a>, and if you are still stuck, then head over to the <a href="http://blackberry.forums.wordpress.org">forums</a> and post as many details as possible so we can help track down the issue.</p>\n<div class="tweetmeme-button" id="tweetmeme-button-post-137">	\n\n\n</div>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=blackberry.wordpress.org&blog=8247031&post=137&subd=wpblackberry&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 28 Jul 2009 20:30:10 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:16:"Raanan Bar-Cohen";}s:7:"summary";s:3131:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>Hi everyone !  Things are progressing nicely with this beta test thanks to everyone who has posted on the <a href="http://blackberry.forums.wordpress.org/">forums</a> and on <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/">trac</a>.  We really appreciate all the feedback and time spent by all of you beta testers.</p>\n<p>Today we have a new beta, version 0.9.0.140 for you to <a href="http://blackberry.wordpress.org/install">download</a>.  Changes include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Improving response time of the user interface <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/58">(ticket #58 UI response time</a>)</li>\n<li>Removingthe photo multimedia option in the app because photo settings are managed in the main BlackBerry camera app</li>\n<li>Fixing a bug with <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/57">local drafts (ticket #57)</a></li>\n<li>Adding prompts to save post when clicking <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/59">&#8220;Back&#8221; button (ticket #59)</a></li>\n<li>Fixing a bug involving <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/60">categories (ticket #60)</a></li>\n<li>Fixing how <a href="http://blackberry.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/61">private posts were not publishing correctly (ticket #61)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>We are also aware that some of you prefer to use this app connecting with BIS.  We are actively working on a solution for this with RIM, but currently don&#8217;t have an ETA for that.</p>\n<p>And as always, please do no post comments to this post involving support or troubleshooting.  If you are having issues, please first review the <a href="http://blackberry.wordpress.org/faq/">FAQ</a>, and if you are still stuck, then head over to the <a href="http://blackberry.forums.wordpress.org">forums</a> and post as many details as possible so we can help track down the issue.</p>\n<div class="tweetmeme-button" id="tweetmeme-button-post-137">	\n\n\n</div>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpblackberry.wordpress.com/137/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=blackberry.wordpress.org&blog=8247031&post=137&subd=wpblackberry&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:24;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:19:"Matt: Bezos Reviews";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=14402";s:4:"link";s:35:"http://ma.tt/2009/07/bezos-reviews/";s:11:"description";s:448:"<p><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/cdp/member-reviews/A2KEKKJ9CAC2KC/ref=cm_pdp_rev_title_2?ie=UTF8&amp;sort%5Fby=MostRecentReview#R1D8ARPBA73LYE">Amazon.com reviews from Jeffrey P. Bezos</a>. Includes milk, cookies, cheese snacks, binoculars, and a Cory Doctorow novel. Unfortunately, the cookie items reviewed are no longer available so we&#8217;re not able to share in &#8220;snickerdoodles [that] were the best I&#8217;ve ever had.&#8221;</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 28 Jul 2009 13:26:28 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:448:"<p><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/cdp/member-reviews/A2KEKKJ9CAC2KC/ref=cm_pdp_rev_title_2?ie=UTF8&amp;sort%5Fby=MostRecentReview#R1D8ARPBA73LYE">Amazon.com reviews from Jeffrey P. Bezos</a>. Includes milk, cookies, cheese snacks, binoculars, and a Cory Doctorow novel. Unfortunately, the cookie items reviewed are no longer available so we&#8217;re not able to share in &#8220;snickerdoodles [that] were the best I&#8217;ve ever had.&#8221;</p>";}i:25;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:13:"Matt: GPL FUD";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=14400";s:4:"link";s:29:"http://ma.tt/2009/07/gpl-fud/";s:11:"description";s:82:"<p><a href="http://ahren.org/code/bit/gpl-fud-round-n1">GPL FUD round N+1</a>.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 28 Jul 2009 11:19:27 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:82:"<p><a href="http://ahren.org/code/bit/gpl-fud-round-n1">GPL FUD round N+1</a>.</p>";}i:26;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:26:"Matt: Favorite iPhone Apps";s:4:"guid";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=14398";s:4:"link";s:42:"http://ma.tt/2009/07/favorite-iphone-apps/";s:11:"description";s:160:"<p><a href="http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/the_favorite_iphone_apps_of_five_geek_rock_stars.php">The Favorite iPhone Apps of Five Geek Rock Stars</a>.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 27 Jul 2009 23:24:46 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:160:"<p><a href="http://www.readwriteweb.com/archives/the_favorite_iphone_apps_of_five_geek_rock_stars.php">The Favorite iPhone Apps of Five Geek Rock Stars</a>.</p>";}i:27;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:60:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/27";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6303";s:4:"link";s:88:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/27/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0727/";s:11:"description";s:3769:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://sivel.net/wordpress/ajax-plugin-helper/">Ajax Plugin Helper</a></p>\n<p>An Ajax Plugin Helper for the WordPress admin plugin page. Adds Ajax activate, deactivate, delete and upgrade functionality.</p>\n<p><a href="http://epicalex.com/gravajax-registration/">Gravajax Registration</a></p>\n<p>A simple plugin that adds a <a href="http://gravatar.com/">gravatar</a> to your blog registration page, which automatically updates when an email is entered into the field.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sillybean.net/code/wordpress/recent-posts-with-excerpts/">Recent Posts with Excerpts</a></p>\n<p>A widget that lists your most recent posts with excerpts, optionally limited to a category. The number of posts and excerpts is configurable; for example, you could show five posts but include the excerpt for only the most recent. Supports <a href="http://robsnotebook.com/the-excerpt-reloaded/">the_excerpt Reloaded</a> and <a href="http://sparepencil.com/code/advanced-excerpt/">Advanced Excerpt</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-change-template/">WP Change Template</a></p>\n<p>The plugin allows to change theme (template) on desired dates. If you want a Christmas theme automatically on your blog just for 5 days (or more), the plugin will do it for you.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.bos89.nl/wordpress-charted-archives-plugin/">Charted Archives</a></p>\n<p>Show your archives by month in a bar chart, after an idea from John Nunemaker.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/flash-video-resizer/">Flash Video Resizer</a></p>\n<p>Resize flash video to a specific size without having to edit HTML code.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/wp-ajax-edit-comments/">WP Ajax Edit Comments</a></p>\n<p>WP Ajax Edit Comments allows users and admins to edit comments on a post. Users can edit their own comments for a limited time, while admins can edit all comments.</p>\n<p><a href="http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/top-10/">Top 10</a></p>\n<p>Top 10 will count the number of page views on your single posts on a daily as well as overall basis. You can then display the page view count on individual posts and pages as well as display a list of most popular posts based on page views.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.samuelfolkes.com/projects/geosmart/">GeoSmart</a></p>\n<p>GeoSmart is a plugin for WordPress which allows you to determine where in the world the people who comment on your posts are located based on their IP addresses.</p>\n<p><a href="http://didier.lorphelin.free.fr/blog/index.php/wordpress/sabre/">Sabre</a></p>\n<p>Sabre is an acronym for Simple Anti Bot Registration Engine. It&#8217;s a set of counter measures against spam registration on your blog.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/wordpress-seo/">SEO Ultimate</a></p>\n<p>This SEO plugin can handle titles, meta, noindex, canonical tags, 404 monitoring, and linkboxes. Version 0.8 fixes bugs and adds robots.txt/htaccess editor tools.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sudarmuthu.com/wordpress/bulk-delete">Bulk Delete</a></p>\n<p>Bulk Delete WordPress Plugin which lets you to delete posts in bulk from selected categories or tags has been updated to version 0.6. In 0.6 you can now bulk delete pending as well as scheduled posts.</p>\n<p><a href="http://scribu.net/wordpress/custom-field-images">Custom Field Images</a></p>\n<p>Allows you to easily associate an image to a post and display it anywhere you like.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/27/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0727/">WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/27</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 27 Jul 2009 22:30:09 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:3769:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://sivel.net/wordpress/ajax-plugin-helper/">Ajax Plugin Helper</a></p>\n<p>An Ajax Plugin Helper for the WordPress admin plugin page. Adds Ajax activate, deactivate, delete and upgrade functionality.</p>\n<p><a href="http://epicalex.com/gravajax-registration/">Gravajax Registration</a></p>\n<p>A simple plugin that adds a <a href="http://gravatar.com/">gravatar</a> to your blog registration page, which automatically updates when an email is entered into the field.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sillybean.net/code/wordpress/recent-posts-with-excerpts/">Recent Posts with Excerpts</a></p>\n<p>A widget that lists your most recent posts with excerpts, optionally limited to a category. The number of posts and excerpts is configurable; for example, you could show five posts but include the excerpt for only the most recent. Supports <a href="http://robsnotebook.com/the-excerpt-reloaded/">the_excerpt Reloaded</a> and <a href="http://sparepencil.com/code/advanced-excerpt/">Advanced Excerpt</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-change-template/">WP Change Template</a></p>\n<p>The plugin allows to change theme (template) on desired dates. If you want a Christmas theme automatically on your blog just for 5 days (or more), the plugin will do it for you.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.bos89.nl/wordpress-charted-archives-plugin/">Charted Archives</a></p>\n<p>Show your archives by month in a bar chart, after an idea from John Nunemaker.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/flash-video-resizer/">Flash Video Resizer</a></p>\n<p>Resize flash video to a specific size without having to edit HTML code.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/wp-ajax-edit-comments/">WP Ajax Edit Comments</a></p>\n<p>WP Ajax Edit Comments allows users and admins to edit comments on a post. Users can edit their own comments for a limited time, while admins can edit all comments.</p>\n<p><a href="http://ajaydsouza.com/wordpress/plugins/top-10/">Top 10</a></p>\n<p>Top 10 will count the number of page views on your single posts on a daily as well as overall basis. You can then display the page view count on individual posts and pages as well as display a list of most popular posts based on page views.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.samuelfolkes.com/projects/geosmart/">GeoSmart</a></p>\n<p>GeoSmart is a plugin for WordPress which allows you to determine where in the world the people who comment on your posts are located based on their IP addresses.</p>\n<p><a href="http://didier.lorphelin.free.fr/blog/index.php/wordpress/sabre/">Sabre</a></p>\n<p>Sabre is an acronym for Simple Anti Bot Registration Engine. It&#8217;s a set of counter measures against spam registration on your blog.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/wordpress-seo/">SEO Ultimate</a></p>\n<p>This SEO plugin can handle titles, meta, noindex, canonical tags, 404 monitoring, and linkboxes. Version 0.8 fixes bugs and adds robots.txt/htaccess editor tools.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sudarmuthu.com/wordpress/bulk-delete">Bulk Delete</a></p>\n<p>Bulk Delete WordPress Plugin which lets you to delete posts in bulk from selected categories or tags has been updated to version 0.6. In 0.6 you can now bulk delete pending as well as scheduled posts.</p>\n<p><a href="http://scribu.net/wordpress/custom-field-images">Custom Field Images</a></p>\n<p>Allows you to easily associate an image to a post and display it anywhere you like.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/27/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0727/">WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/27</a></p>";}i:28;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:45:"WP iPhone: Your Most Interesting Mobile Post?";s:4:"guid";s:34:"http://iphone.wordpress.org/?p=412";s:4:"link";s:73:"http://iphone.wordpress.org/2009/07/27/your-most-interesting-mobile-post/";s:11:"description";s:2296:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>So here&#8217;s a question for the mobile bloggers out there.  What has been your most unique, or most memorable mobile post?  Whether it was posting from Kazakhstan while riding steppe ponies, from under your car while changing your oil, or the best prose you&#8217;ve written while blogging from your iPhone &#8212; add a comment and let us know.</p>\n<p>Keep it G-rated and come back from time to time to see what others have shared.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ll start off by sharing a not-very exciting example.  Recently I took the family to Zion&#8217;s National Park and we were briefly rained &#8220;in&#8221; at the main building.  Being the OCD developer that I am, I turned my wife and kids loose in the souvenir store and began testing some code I had recently written by posting several brief entries to my blog.  They consisted mostly of &#8220;test 1&#8243; and &#8220;test 1&#8243; but hey &#8211; that&#8217;s the kind of exciting life I live&#8230;  So, the location was a bit interesting, the prose &#8211; not.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m sure many of you can top that (not hard!) so drop a comment and get the ball rolling!</p>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=iphone.wordpress.org&blog=3882653&post=412&subd=wpiphone&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 27 Jul 2009 04:56:52 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:16:"John Bickerstaff";}s:7:"summary";s:2296:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>So here&#8217;s a question for the mobile bloggers out there.  What has been your most unique, or most memorable mobile post?  Whether it was posting from Kazakhstan while riding steppe ponies, from under your car while changing your oil, or the best prose you&#8217;ve written while blogging from your iPhone &#8212; add a comment and let us know.</p>\n<p>Keep it G-rated and come back from time to time to see what others have shared.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ll start off by sharing a not-very exciting example.  Recently I took the family to Zion&#8217;s National Park and we were briefly rained &#8220;in&#8221; at the main building.  Being the OCD developer that I am, I turned my wife and kids loose in the souvenir store and began testing some code I had recently written by posting several brief entries to my blog.  They consisted mostly of &#8220;test 1&#8243; and &#8220;test 1&#8243; but hey &#8211; that&#8217;s the kind of exciting life I live&#8230;  So, the location was a bit interesting, the prose &#8211; not.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m sure many of you can top that (not hard!) so drop a comment and get the ball rolling!</p>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/412/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=iphone.wordpress.org&blog=3882653&post=412&subd=wpiphone&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:29;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:46:"WP iPhone: Thanks for Help Testing XML-RPC Fix";s:4:"guid";s:34:"http://iphone.wordpress.org/?p=409";s:4:"link";s:75:"http://iphone.wordpress.org/2009/07/27/thanks-for-help-testing-xml-rpc-fix/";s:11:"description";s:2042:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>As you may have seen in a recent post, I asked for volunteers to help me test my code fix for the issue where the iPhone app couldn&#8217;t find the XMLRPC endpoint for a blog.  Around 15 l brave volunteers stepped forward and I&#8217;m glad to report that in those cases where that specific problem was the issue, the new code allowed the app to get to the endpoint successfully.</p>\n<p>Many thanks to the volunteers for answering e-mails and changing settings etc.  This fix will be going into the next release.</p>\n<p>For those who enjoy detail &#8211; the new code avoids using an XML parse to find the information and instead goes after it directly with a couple of regular expressions.  In the rare case where this does not find the endpoint, the application gives the user an opportunity to enter the XML-RPC endpoint directly via a new screen in the application.</p>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=iphone.wordpress.org&blog=3882653&post=409&subd=wpiphone&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 27 Jul 2009 04:34:52 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:16:"John Bickerstaff";}s:7:"summary";s:2042:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><p>As you may have seen in a recent post, I asked for volunteers to help me test my code fix for the issue where the iPhone app couldn&#8217;t find the XMLRPC endpoint for a blog.  Around 15 l brave volunteers stepped forward and I&#8217;m glad to report that in those cases where that specific problem was the issue, the new code allowed the app to get to the endpoint successfully.</p>\n<p>Many thanks to the volunteers for answering e-mails and changing settings etc.  This fix will be going into the next release.</p>\n<p>For those who enjoy detail &#8211; the new code avoids using an XML parse to find the information and instead goes after it directly with a couple of regular expressions.  In the rare case where this does not find the endpoint, the application gives the user an opportunity to enter the XML-RPC endpoint directly via a new screen in the application.</p>\n  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wpiphone.wordpress.com/409/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=iphone.wordpress.org&blog=3882653&post=409&subd=wpiphone&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:30;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:67:"WordPress.tv: Introducing Gravatar: Your Globally Recognized Avatar";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2155";s:4:"link";s:84:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/26/introducing-gravatar-your-globally-recognized-avatar/";s:11:"description";s:1404:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-1">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/26/introducing-gravatar-your-globally-recognized-avatar/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/UyDfmflZ/gravatar-intro-h264_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2155&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sun, 26 Jul 2009 06:46:39 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:12:"Michael Pick";}s:7:"summary";s:1404:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-1">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/26/introducing-gravatar-your-globally-recognized-avatar/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/UyDfmflZ/gravatar-intro-h264_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/2155/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=2155&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" /></div>";}i:31;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:59:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 07/25";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6300";s:4:"link";s:89:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/25/wordpress-theme-releases-for-0725-2/";s:11:"description";s:2472:"<p><a href="http://brandonwang.org/wp/stsi">Stunning Silence</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://wp-themes.com/stunning-silence/"><img title="StunningSilence" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/StunningSilence.gif" alt="StunningSilence" width="200" height="129" /></a></p>\n<p>Stunning Silence: it&#8217;s an amazing and customizable WordPress theme. It&#8217;s got lots of goodies like a huge options page, a great Twitter integration (straight in the header!), artful and delicious color schemes, but on the outside, all your visitors will see is a beautiful, modern, simple, and stylish theme, putting the spotlight on your work</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.colixiodesign.com/en/2009/palmixio-tema-wordpress-100-free-widget-ready-in-italiano/">Palmixio</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.colixiodesign.com/themes/?preview_theme=Palmixio"><img title="Palmixio" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/Palmixio.png" alt="Palmixio" width="200" height="152" /></a></p>\n<p>Palmixio is a theme for Wordpress, its features : two columns, widget ready (sidebar and footer), custom gravatar, flexible width, threaded comments, easy to customize.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.espreson.com/2009/07/12/free-wordpress-theme-evr-green/">Evr Green</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.espreson.com/espresontheme/?wptheme=evr-green"><img title="Evr Green" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/EvrGreen.png" alt="Evr Green" width="200" height="150" /></a></p>\n<p>Evr Green a free magazine styled wordpress theme, enabled with personal Twitter updates, social bookmarking, tabbed content, email subscription, and lots more.</p>\n<p><a href="http://themocracy.com/2009/05/folders-free-wordpress-theme/">OfficeFolders</a></p>\n<p><img title="OfficeFolders" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/OfficeFolders.png" alt="OfficeFolders" width="200" height="149" /></p>\n<p>OfficeFolders is a blue, grey and white, widget ready two-column theme with a right sidebar.</p>\n<p>Are you a theme author? Learn how you can <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/submit-news/">submit your theme</a> and get listed in these releases.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/25/wordpress-theme-releases-for-0725-2/">WordPress Theme Releases for 07/25</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 25 Jul 2009 19:29:44 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:2472:"<p><a href="http://brandonwang.org/wp/stsi">Stunning Silence</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://wp-themes.com/stunning-silence/"><img title="StunningSilence" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/StunningSilence.gif" alt="StunningSilence" width="200" height="129" /></a></p>\n<p>Stunning Silence: it&#8217;s an amazing and customizable WordPress theme. It&#8217;s got lots of goodies like a huge options page, a great Twitter integration (straight in the header!), artful and delicious color schemes, but on the outside, all your visitors will see is a beautiful, modern, simple, and stylish theme, putting the spotlight on your work</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.colixiodesign.com/en/2009/palmixio-tema-wordpress-100-free-widget-ready-in-italiano/">Palmixio</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.colixiodesign.com/themes/?preview_theme=Palmixio"><img title="Palmixio" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/Palmixio.png" alt="Palmixio" width="200" height="152" /></a></p>\n<p>Palmixio is a theme for Wordpress, its features : two columns, widget ready (sidebar and footer), custom gravatar, flexible width, threaded comments, easy to customize.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.espreson.com/2009/07/12/free-wordpress-theme-evr-green/">Evr Green</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.espreson.com/espresontheme/?wptheme=evr-green"><img title="Evr Green" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/EvrGreen.png" alt="Evr Green" width="200" height="150" /></a></p>\n<p>Evr Green a free magazine styled wordpress theme, enabled with personal Twitter updates, social bookmarking, tabbed content, email subscription, and lots more.</p>\n<p><a href="http://themocracy.com/2009/05/folders-free-wordpress-theme/">OfficeFolders</a></p>\n<p><img title="OfficeFolders" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/OfficeFolders.png" alt="OfficeFolders" width="200" height="149" /></p>\n<p>OfficeFolders is a blue, grey and white, widget ready two-column theme with a right sidebar.</p>\n<p>Are you a theme author? Learn how you can <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/submit-news/">submit your theme</a> and get listed in these releases.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/25/wordpress-theme-releases-for-0725-2/">WordPress Theme Releases for 07/25</a></p>";}i:32;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:72:"Weblog Tools Collection: Send in your entries to the Plugin Competition!";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6294";s:4:"link";s:100:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/24/send-in-your-entries-to-the-plugin-competition/";s:11:"description";s:2092:"<p>There are now over 30 posts about new plugins on the <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/pluginblog/">WordPress Plugin Competition blog</a> if you have not checked them out already. The <strong>prize purse stands at about $3000</strong> thanks to some <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/06/01/plugin-competition-prizes/">generous sponsors and well wishers</a>. But the competition is about to come to a close.</p>\n<p>As promised, please send in your entries to the following email in the following format:</p>\n<p>Plugin Competition Entry Submission Email: <strong>wpplugincomp@wltc.net</strong></p>\n<p>Subject: <strong>WordPress Plugin Competition 2009 Entry: [Name of your Plugin]</strong></p>\n<p>Body: <strong>[Your Name] [Your Email Address] [Your Paypal Address] [Plugin Competition Blog Post about your plugin] [Plugin Description] [Blog/website Address]</strong></p>\n<p>Attachment: <strong>[a zip file containing the final version of your plugin to be considered for judging]</strong></p>\n<p>If you have not done so already, please register on the Plugin Blog and post your entry on the blog so our readers can vote on them (did you vote on the plugins yet?). Then once your have all your bugs worked out and features tweaked, send us the final copy. We will receive entries till 11:59 PM on the 1st of August.</p>\n<p><strong>Thank you to all the Plugin Authors for participating in the competition. If you know of a plugin author who should participate, please send them the required links. If you need ideas for a plugin to enter into the competition, check out our post &#8220;<a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/19/what-would-you-like-in-a-wordpress-plugin/">What would you like in a WordPress plugin?</a>&#8221; </strong></p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/24/send-in-your-entries-to-the-plugin-competition/">Send in your entries to the Plugin Competition!</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 24 Jul 2009 22:02:18 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:10:"Mark Ghosh";}s:7:"summary";s:2092:"<p>There are now over 30 posts about new plugins on the <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/pluginblog/">WordPress Plugin Competition blog</a> if you have not checked them out already. The <strong>prize purse stands at about $3000</strong> thanks to some <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/06/01/plugin-competition-prizes/">generous sponsors and well wishers</a>. But the competition is about to come to a close.</p>\n<p>As promised, please send in your entries to the following email in the following format:</p>\n<p>Plugin Competition Entry Submission Email: <strong>wpplugincomp@wltc.net</strong></p>\n<p>Subject: <strong>WordPress Plugin Competition 2009 Entry: [Name of your Plugin]</strong></p>\n<p>Body: <strong>[Your Name] [Your Email Address] [Your Paypal Address] [Plugin Competition Blog Post about your plugin] [Plugin Description] [Blog/website Address]</strong></p>\n<p>Attachment: <strong>[a zip file containing the final version of your plugin to be considered for judging]</strong></p>\n<p>If you have not done so already, please register on the Plugin Blog and post your entry on the blog so our readers can vote on them (did you vote on the plugins yet?). Then once your have all your bugs worked out and features tweaked, send us the final copy. We will receive entries till 11:59 PM on the 1st of August.</p>\n<p><strong>Thank you to all the Plugin Authors for participating in the competition. If you know of a plugin author who should participate, please send them the required links. If you need ideas for a plugin to enter into the competition, check out our post &#8220;<a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/19/what-would-you-like-in-a-wordpress-plugin/">What would you like in a WordPress plugin?</a>&#8221; </strong></p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/24/send-in-your-entries-to-the-plugin-competition/">Send in your entries to the Plugin Competition!</a></p>";}i:33;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:42:"Alex King: Mac Text Editor WordPress Tools";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://alexking.org/?p=3503";s:4:"link";s:67:"http://alexking.org/blog/2009/07/24/mac-text-editor-wordpress-tools";s:11:"description";s:1978:"<p><a href="http://top-frog.com" rel="external">Shawn</a> (one of our talented developers at <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com">Crowd Favorite</a>) has created some great tools for WordPress developers that use BBEdit and TextMate. The <a href="http://top-frog.com/projects/wordpress-textmate-bundle/" rel="external">TextMate bundle</a> has been out for a little while, but he now has a functional <a href="http://top-frog.com/2009/07/24/wordpress-clippings-bundle-for-bbedit/" rel="external">port of it to a BBEdit clipping set as well</a>.<sup><a href="http://alexking.org/blog/topic/wordpress/feed#fn1248450602713n" id="fn1248450602713" class="footnote">1</a></sup></p>\n<p class="center"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/alexkingorg/3752692654/" title="BBEdit WordPress Clippings by alexkingorg, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3516/3752692654_22d860e85e_o.png" width="262" height="178" alt="BBEdit WordPress Clippings" /></a></p>\n<p>The TextMate Bundle provides nice, handy auto-complete functionality (with code hints) for core WordPress functions within TextMate. The BBEdit Clipping Set does the same thing for BBEdit users. Of course, there is full support for the <a href="http://carringtontheme.com">Carrington</a> CMS theme framework as well. This should be really handy for both plugin developers and theme authors.</p>\n<p>These are open source and hosted on <a href="http://github.com/Gipetto" rel="external">Github</a>, so any enhancements, etc. from the community are welcome.</p>\n<p>I can&#8217;t wait to do some more coding and see how best to use the new clippings.</p>\n<ol class="footnotes">\n<li id="fn1248450602713n">The TextMate version is more tested and mature, but with some encouragement I think he&#8217;ll polish up the BBEdit version as well. [<a href="http://alexking.org/blog/topic/wordpress/feed#fn1248450602713">back</a>]</li>\n</ol>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=3503&type=feed" alt="" />";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 24 Jul 2009 16:03:46 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Alex";}s:7:"summary";s:1978:"<p><a href="http://top-frog.com" rel="external">Shawn</a> (one of our talented developers at <a href="http://crowdfavorite.com">Crowd Favorite</a>) has created some great tools for WordPress developers that use BBEdit and TextMate. The <a href="http://top-frog.com/projects/wordpress-textmate-bundle/" rel="external">TextMate bundle</a> has been out for a little while, but he now has a functional <a href="http://top-frog.com/2009/07/24/wordpress-clippings-bundle-for-bbedit/" rel="external">port of it to a BBEdit clipping set as well</a>.<sup><a href="http://alexking.org/blog/topic/wordpress/feed#fn1248450602713n" id="fn1248450602713" class="footnote">1</a></sup></p>\n<p class="center"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/alexkingorg/3752692654/" title="BBEdit WordPress Clippings by alexkingorg, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3516/3752692654_22d860e85e_o.png" width="262" height="178" alt="BBEdit WordPress Clippings" /></a></p>\n<p>The TextMate Bundle provides nice, handy auto-complete functionality (with code hints) for core WordPress functions within TextMate. The BBEdit Clipping Set does the same thing for BBEdit users. Of course, there is full support for the <a href="http://carringtontheme.com">Carrington</a> CMS theme framework as well. This should be really handy for both plugin developers and theme authors.</p>\n<p>These are open source and hosted on <a href="http://github.com/Gipetto" rel="external">Github</a>, so any enhancements, etc. from the community are welcome.</p>\n<p>I can&#8217;t wait to do some more coding and see how best to use the new clippings.</p>\n<ol class="footnotes">\n<li id="fn1248450602713n">The TextMate version is more tested and mature, but with some encouragement I think he&#8217;ll polish up the BBEdit version as well. [<a href="http://alexking.org/blog/topic/wordpress/feed#fn1248450602713">back</a>]</li>\n</ol>\n<img src="http://alexking.org/wp/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=3503&type=feed" alt="" />";}i:34;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:48:"WordPress.tv: WordPress.com – Widgets Overview";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2178";s:4:"link";s:45:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/24/wpcom-widgets/";s:11:"description";s:1361:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-2">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/24/wpcom-widgets/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/vk0UzFjq/widgets-com-web_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2178/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/commen