re, fix a security problem or change something with your plugin, rest assured your plugin users will be intimated about it without you having to break your head and contacting each and every user, which is impossible by the way.</p>\n<h3>What Else?</h3>\n<p>Did I miss anything? Will you add your plugins to the WordPress Extend, now that you know the benefits? I would like to hear from you, the discussion is now open, so go ahead and let your thoughts be known.</p>\n<p><em>P.S. One thing I would like to suggest WordPress plugin developers is to add a changelog to their plugins, read </em><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/06/20/attention-all-plugin-authors/"><em>why adding changelog matters</em></a><em> also check out the blog post </em><a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2009/07/improving-your-plugin-changelogs/"><em>Improving your plugin – Changelogs</em></a><em> from the WordPress development blog. </em></p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/benefits-of-adding-plugin-to-wordpress-extend/">Why Should You Add Your Plugin to WordPress Extend?</a></p>";}i:38;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:72:"Weblog Tools Collection: Create Private Twitter Like Site With WordPress";s:4:"guid";s:101:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/create-private-twitter-like-site-with-wordpress/";s:4:"link";s:101:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/create-private-twitter-like-site-with-wordpress/";s:11:"description";s:856:"<p>Twitter is definitely becoming popular day by day, by far it is one of the most easiest way to communicate with others.</p>\n<p>If you want to create a site similar to twitter, Cats Who Code has a excellent step by step tutorial that will help you <a href="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Catswhocode/~3/gEyKRW09jDc/create-your-own-private-twitter-site-using-wordpress">create a private twitter site using WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>BTW if you are on twitter, don’t forget to follow us <a href="http://twitter.com/weblogtooltips">@weblogtooltips</a>.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/create-private-twitter-like-site-with-wordpress/">Create Private Twitter Like Site With WordPress</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 23 Jul 2009 21:13:22 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:12:"Keith Dsouza";}s:7:"summary";s:856:"<p>Twitter is definitely becoming popular day by day, by far it is one of the most easiest way to communicate with others.</p>\n<p>If you want to create a site similar to twitter, Cats Who Code has a excellent step by step tutorial that will help you <a href="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Catswhocode/~3/gEyKRW09jDc/create-your-own-private-twitter-site-using-wordpress">create a private twitter site using WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>BTW if you are on twitter, don’t forget to follow us <a href="http://twitter.com/weblogtooltips">@weblogtooltips</a>.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/create-private-twitter-like-site-with-wordpress/">Create Private Twitter Like Site With WordPress</a></p>";}i:39;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:60:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/23";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=6287";s:4:"link";s:88:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0723/";s:11:"description";s:3581:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://blog.kirb.us/wordpress-plugin-user-count/">User Count</a></p>\n<p>Simply displays the number of users who have an account on your blog on the admin dashboard. Also lists number of users by user role.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sudarmuthu.com/wordpress/easy-retweet">Easy ReTweet</a></p>\n<p>Easy ReTweet is a WordPress Plugin, which let’s you add retweet or Tweet this buttons for your WordPress posts, together with the retweet count.</p>\n<p><a href="http://nspeaks.com/671/indian-sociable-wordpress-plugin-released/">Indian Sociable Plugin</a></p>\n<p>Indian Sociable Plugin can instantly add the most popular Indian Sociable Bookmarking Sites on to your blog. Currently it supports 9 Popular Indian Bookmarking Sites. It is based on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/sociable">Sociable Plugin by Joost</a>. Requires it to be installed first(3.4 version and above only).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ericlightbody.com/tweetiepie">TweetiePie</a></p>\n<p>TweetiePie&#8217;s purpose in life is to bring in your most recent updates from twitter and put them on WordPress. It properly linkifies hash tags, @replies, and URLs. This can be done by using a widget or as a direct function call. It’s super-easy to get your tweets on the sidebar. Simply supply your username, how many tweets you would like to display, and whether or not you would like to show the date.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.superlevel.de/wordpress/wpsuperfeedbox">WPSuperFeedBox</a></p>\n<p>Adds a fancy hideable Feed Box to your Post Page and boosts your subscriber count.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/wordpress-seo/">SEO Ultimate</a></p>\n<p>This SEO plugin can handle titles, meta, noindex, canonical tags, 404 monitoring, and linkboxes. Version 0.7 adds a Module Manager.</p>\n<p><a href="http://coffee2code.com/wp-plugins/loop-post-navigation-links/">Loop Post Navigation Links</a></p>\n<p>Template tags (for use in single.php) to create post navigation loop (previous to first post is last post; next/after last post is first post).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.viadat.com/store-locator">Store Locator</a></p>\n<p>The Store Locator plugin empowers web developers &amp; web site owners to easily manage and display any set of important stores, products, or other locations on their website in an easily searchable manner. Uses Google Maps.</p>\n<p><a href="http://striderweb.com/nerdaphernalia/features/virtual-multiblog/">Virtual Multiblog</a></p>\n<p>Virtual Multiblog allows you to run more than one blog off a single install of WordPress. Each blog is managed as a completely separate install &#8212; separate admin sections, separate users, etc. They will happily co-exist with different themes and plugins activated. The biggest advantage is that you will only have to keep one set of program files up-to-date, and this method should be expandable to as many different blogs as you like.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/geotagphoto/">GeotagPhoto</a></p>\n<p>Geotagged photos are automatically given a link to show where they were taken in the google map.</p>\n<p><a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/sociable/">Sociable</a></p>\n<p>Automatically add links on your posts, pages and RSS feed to your favorite social bookmarking sites.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0723/">WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/23</a></p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 23 Jul 2009 19:58:10 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:7:"Perurry";}s:7:"summary";s:3581:"<h3>New Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://blog.kirb.us/wordpress-plugin-user-count/">User Count</a></p>\n<p>Simply displays the number of users who have an account on your blog on the admin dashboard. Also lists number of users by user role.</p>\n<p><a href="http://sudarmuthu.com/wordpress/easy-retweet">Easy ReTweet</a></p>\n<p>Easy ReTweet is a WordPress Plugin, which let’s you add retweet or Tweet this buttons for your WordPress posts, together with the retweet count.</p>\n<p><a href="http://nspeaks.com/671/indian-sociable-wordpress-plugin-released/">Indian Sociable Plugin</a></p>\n<p>Indian Sociable Plugin can instantly add the most popular Indian Sociable Bookmarking Sites on to your blog. Currently it supports 9 Popular Indian Bookmarking Sites. It is based on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/sociable">Sociable Plugin by Joost</a>. Requires it to be installed first(3.4 version and above only).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ericlightbody.com/tweetiepie">TweetiePie</a></p>\n<p>TweetiePie&#8217;s purpose in life is to bring in your most recent updates from twitter and put them on WordPress. It properly linkifies hash tags, @replies, and URLs. This can be done by using a widget or as a direct function call. It’s super-easy to get your tweets on the sidebar. Simply supply your username, how many tweets you would like to display, and whether or not you would like to show the date.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.superlevel.de/wordpress/wpsuperfeedbox">WPSuperFeedBox</a></p>\n<p>Adds a fancy hideable Feed Box to your Post Page and boosts your subscriber count.</p>\n<h3>Updated Plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/wordpress-seo/">SEO Ultimate</a></p>\n<p>This SEO plugin can handle titles, meta, noindex, canonical tags, 404 monitoring, and linkboxes. Version 0.7 adds a Module Manager.</p>\n<p><a href="http://coffee2code.com/wp-plugins/loop-post-navigation-links/">Loop Post Navigation Links</a></p>\n<p>Template tags (for use in single.php) to create post navigation loop (previous to first post is last post; next/after last post is first post).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.viadat.com/store-locator">Store Locator</a></p>\n<p>The Store Locator plugin empowers web developers &amp; web site owners to easily manage and display any set of important stores, products, or other locations on their website in an easily searchable manner. Uses Google Maps.</p>\n<p><a href="http://striderweb.com/nerdaphernalia/features/virtual-multiblog/">Virtual Multiblog</a></p>\n<p>Virtual Multiblog allows you to run more than one blog off a single install of WordPress. Each blog is managed as a completely separate install &#8212; separate admin sections, separate users, etc. They will happily co-exist with different themes and plugins activated. The biggest advantage is that you will only have to keep one set of program files up-to-date, and this method should be expandable to as many different blogs as you like.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/geotagphoto/">GeotagPhoto</a></p>\n<p>Geotagged photos are automatically given a link to show where they were taken in the google map.</p>\n<p><a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/sociable/">Sociable</a></p>\n<p>Automatically add links on your posts, pages and RSS feed to your favorite social bookmarking sites.</p>\n<p>Post from: <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com">Weblog Tools Collection</a><br />><br /></a><br /><br />><br /></a><br /><br /><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/07/23/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-0723/">WordPress Plugin Releases for 07/23</a></p>";}i:40;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:75:"WordPress.tv: WordPress.com – Adding Your Twitter Updates to Your Sidebar";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wordpress.tv/?p=2167";s:4:"link";s:89:"http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/22/wordpress-com-adding-your-twitter-updates-to-your-sidebar/";s:11:"description";s:1402:"<div class="snap_preview"><br /><ins>\n<div class="video-player" id="x-video-4">\n </div></ins>\n<br /><a href="http://wordpress.tv/2009/07/22/wordpress-com-adding-your-twitter-updates-to-your-sidebar/"><img width="160" height="120" src="http://cdn.videos.wordpress.com/BAlGeRbn/wpcomtwitter_std.original.jpg" /> </a>  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/2167/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/2167/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/2167/"><img alt="" border="0" src="htt